1
00:00:02,381 --> 00:00:03,502
[thuds]

2
00:00:03,672 --> 00:00:04,673
Surrender.

3
00:00:05,054 --> 00:00:07,506
You are the last hill giant
standing, Dantak.

4
00:00:08,057 --> 00:00:10,599
We've left you alone,
so why attack us?

5
00:00:11,059 --> 00:00:12,351
[VAN]
Because of your sloth.

6
00:00:13,141 --> 00:00:14,473
[DANTAK] Nonsense.

7
00:00:15,013 --> 00:00:16,314
On that, we can agree.

8
00:00:16,515 --> 00:00:17,896
Monsters who won't kill?

9
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:19,938
Who just cower in their lairs?

10
00:00:20,398 --> 00:00:22,110
You defy Lord Demis' will.

11
00:00:23,151 --> 00:00:25,193
[DANTAK]
Who are you, boy?

12
00:00:26,985 --> 00:00:28,276
Slayer of evil.

13
00:00:28,946 --> 00:00:29,947
Van the Hero.

14
00:00:30,988 --> 00:00:32,120
The Hero?

15
00:00:32,830 --> 00:00:34,532
You're nothing but a child!

16
00:00:34,622 --> 00:00:35,623
[slashing]

17
00:00:38,335 --> 00:00:40,377
[blood splattering]

18
00:00:40,538 --> 00:00:41,789
[VAN]
Begone now, evil.

19
00:00:42,039 --> 00:00:44,091
Yay! Isn't he great?

20
00:00:44,842 --> 00:00:47,094
-A maniac. Perfect.
-[squealing]

21
00:00:47,754 --> 00:00:50,887
♪

22
00:02:25,228 --> 00:02:26,729
-[fire crackling]
-[chuckles]

23
00:02:28,311 --> 00:02:30,393
-Huh?
-Smells tasty, Esta.

24
00:02:30,563 --> 00:02:31,604
Dinner ready?

25
00:02:32,234 --> 00:02:33,606
[ESTA]
Care to join me, Tisse?

26
00:02:34,446 --> 00:02:35,778
Where are the others?

27
00:02:36,608 --> 00:02:39,201
[ESTA] Van and Lavender
went to hunt down monsters.

28
00:02:39,531 --> 00:02:41,453
Cardinal Ljubo
is out like a light.

29
00:02:42,454 --> 00:02:43,495
[chuckles]

30
00:02:43,705 --> 00:02:45,407
Just us? Excellent.

31
00:02:45,577 --> 00:02:48,580
[fire crackling]

32
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:52,003
♪

33
00:02:52,123 --> 00:02:55,216
Remember when we used to sit
around campfires like this?

34
00:02:55,587 --> 00:02:56,588
I do!

35
00:02:57,048 --> 00:02:58,299
Those were good times.

36
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:01,552
But I don't recall you cooking
back then, Miss Theodora.

37
00:03:02,173 --> 00:03:03,764
I picked it up recently.

38
00:03:04,265 --> 00:03:05,976
An enjoyable skill, I've found.

39
00:03:06,097 --> 00:03:07,098
Huh.

40
00:03:07,228 --> 00:03:09,890
Seems to me you're
following in Red's footsteps.

41
00:03:10,311 --> 00:03:11,312
I am.

42
00:03:11,682 --> 00:03:13,314
I wish to be more like him.

43
00:03:13,684 --> 00:03:15,436
Not only in making a meal,

44
00:03:15,776 --> 00:03:17,858
but in supporting
and guiding a Hero.

45
00:03:18,649 --> 00:03:21,942
However, all I've managed
to learn is how much I lack.

46
00:03:22,112 --> 00:03:23,113
It's not you.

47
00:03:23,613 --> 00:03:25,865
I would say it's more
an issue with your Hero.

48
00:03:26,616 --> 00:03:28,748
Albert would be worried
to see you like this.

49
00:03:28,828 --> 00:03:29,829
Huh?!

50
00:03:30,950 --> 00:03:32,121
You have a point.

51
00:03:32,452 --> 00:03:34,294
I fear I've caused him
enough trouble.

52
00:03:34,584 --> 00:03:35,585
That's funny.

53
00:03:35,665 --> 00:03:37,627
Whenever you come up,
he always speaks

54
00:03:37,707 --> 00:03:40,089
about you with such pride,
that it makes me think

55
00:03:40,459 --> 00:03:43,092
he's happy working
alongside you, specifically.

56
00:03:43,382 --> 00:03:46,095
Stop. He can't be
that enthusiastic.

57
00:03:46,515 --> 00:03:47,516
Oh, he is.

58
00:03:47,806 --> 00:03:50,639
He also seemed
to miss you very much.

59
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:52,721
Does he really?

60
00:03:53,021 --> 00:03:54,813
Albert misses me,
of all people?

61
00:03:55,394 --> 00:03:56,395
Me?

62
00:03:56,605 --> 00:03:57,566
-[Mr. Crawly Wally squeals]
-Hm.

63
00:03:57,936 --> 00:03:59,858
I mean,
it's nice to hear, is all.

64
00:04:00,318 --> 00:04:02,731
Very. I suppose
the feeling is mutual.

65
00:04:02,901 --> 00:04:04,482
If I am afforded
the opportunity,

66
00:04:04,572 --> 00:04:06,234
then I would like
to see him soon.

67
00:04:06,484 --> 00:04:07,906
No! I misspoke!

68
00:04:08,576 --> 00:04:10,038
[ESTA]
What am I even saying?

69
00:04:11,239 --> 00:04:12,700
Please do not misunderstand.

70
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:15,243
I merely wish to reunite
with a good friend!

71
00:04:15,453 --> 00:04:16,874
Yes, a good friend,

72
00:04:16,954 --> 00:04:18,246
no more, and no less!

73
00:04:18,586 --> 00:04:20,628
Thank you for the illuminating
discussion.

74
00:04:21,379 --> 00:04:24,171
Well! A fine evening
for a drink, yes?

75
00:04:24,341 --> 00:04:26,553
Indeed! Off to fetch water!

76
00:04:27,925 --> 00:04:28,926
[cloth flutters]

77
00:04:31,008 --> 00:04:32,389
[TISSE]
Someone's in love!

78
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:36,643
♪

79
00:04:36,853 --> 00:04:38,605
-Huh!
-Piping hot curry buns,

80
00:04:38,725 --> 00:04:40,227
the village specialty!

81
00:04:40,727 --> 00:04:42,939
Eat! You three
must be starving!

82
00:04:43,149 --> 00:04:44,981
-Go on. Don't be shy!
-[Rit chuckles]

83
00:04:45,862 --> 00:04:46,863
[chuckles]

84
00:04:47,824 --> 00:04:49,696
Three square meals
of curry a day.

85
00:04:49,776 --> 00:04:51,617
-[RED] Shh.
-[chomps]

86
00:04:51,988 --> 00:04:53,199
[munching]

87
00:04:53,369 --> 00:04:54,370
[chuckles]

88
00:04:54,450 --> 00:04:56,872
This aroma is absolutely
to die for.

89
00:04:56,953 --> 00:04:58,414
And it's spicy!

90
00:04:58,704 --> 00:05:00,626
Fried bread when the day's
only begun?

91
00:05:00,996 --> 00:05:03,088
It feels a bit indulgent
for my taste.

92
00:05:03,379 --> 00:05:04,880
Stuffed with curry, too.

93
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,592
Hence the name, curry bread.

94
00:05:06,672 --> 00:05:08,003
-[FEMALE VILLAGER 208A] Wow!
-Huh.

95
00:05:08,093 --> 00:05:09,044
[FEMALE VILLAGER 208B]
Look, look!

96
00:05:09,174 --> 00:05:10,596
[FEMALE VILLAGER 208A]
That's amazing.

97
00:05:10,676 --> 00:05:11,887
Where are they going?

98
00:05:12,347 --> 00:05:13,468
My, oh, my.

99
00:05:14,009 --> 00:05:16,301
There's a sight
you don't see every day.

100
00:05:16,511 --> 00:05:17,973
A herd of Pegasi.

101
00:05:18,143 --> 00:05:21,266
First time I've ever seen them
flying high over our village.

102
00:05:21,856 --> 00:05:24,148
Almost like the herd's
fleeing for safety.

103
00:05:24,309 --> 00:05:25,310
Hm.

104
00:05:26,150 --> 00:05:27,151
Huh?

105
00:05:27,522 --> 00:05:28,693
Something's coming.

106
00:05:30,064 --> 00:05:33,067
[water gurgling]

107
00:05:37,621 --> 00:05:39,243
[ESTA]
The Fairy King's gem.

108
00:05:39,914 --> 00:05:43,207
That shield allows its wielder
to use mind control magic.

109
00:05:45,999 --> 00:05:47,961
I trust you understand
its influence.

110
00:05:48,041 --> 00:05:49,252
-[LAVENDER] Another lecture?
-Hm.

111
00:05:50,464 --> 00:05:52,335
All you ever do is nag, lady!

112
00:05:53,176 --> 00:05:54,968
That depends
on how one wields it.

113
00:05:55,719 --> 00:05:57,470
If used as a beacon of light,

114
00:05:57,931 --> 00:06:00,763
then it shall guide evildoers
onto the path of faith.

115
00:06:01,394 --> 00:06:03,266
Forcing someone
to their knees in prayer

116
00:06:03,346 --> 00:06:04,767
won't make them a believer.

117
00:06:05,398 --> 00:06:07,190
That beacon should
be sealed away.

118
00:06:08,060 --> 00:06:09,852
Van earned the shield, not you.

119
00:06:09,942 --> 00:06:12,485
So how he uses it
is none of your concern.

120
00:06:12,775 --> 00:06:13,776
[sighs]

121
00:06:14,406 --> 00:06:16,859
♪

122
00:06:16,949 --> 00:06:18,410
[children laughing]

123
00:06:18,611 --> 00:06:20,993
Our only business here
is handing over an airship

124
00:06:21,073 --> 00:06:23,115
to Sir Hero,
and they're throwing a party.

125
00:06:23,615 --> 00:06:25,247
This event has me on edge.

126
00:06:25,367 --> 00:06:27,039
Certainly there won't be
any issues

127
00:06:27,119 --> 00:06:28,460
like our last encounter.

128
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:31,373
What more could a Hero want
than to celebrate in his honor?

129
00:06:31,463 --> 00:06:32,624
-[indistinct chatter]
-Hm.

130
00:06:34,295 --> 00:06:36,127
[MOGRIM]
All right! That should do it.

131
00:06:36,758 --> 00:06:38,009
-[MIDO] Hey, Mogrim!
-Hm?

132
00:06:38,089 --> 00:06:39,801
[chuckles]
How goes the missus?

133
00:06:40,091 --> 00:06:41,843
[MOGRIM] Try as I might
to get her to rest,

134
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:44,095
she won't listen
to a word I say!

135
00:06:44,435 --> 00:06:45,476
Got me all nervous!

136
00:06:46,387 --> 00:06:48,059
Well, it's still early.

137
00:06:48,389 --> 00:06:50,191
Make sure she slows down a bit.

138
00:06:50,271 --> 00:06:53,023
And, of course, be there
for your wife, no matter what.

139
00:06:53,314 --> 00:06:55,646
I got her covered there,
doc, no worries!

140
00:06:56,897 --> 00:06:59,900
[all gulping]

141
00:07:00,821 --> 00:07:01,902
[grunts]

142
00:07:02,532 --> 00:07:04,995
Hey! How's the new gig going,
Godwin?

143
00:07:05,575 --> 00:07:08,248
Starting to make a profit,
thanks to those little zoogs.

144
00:07:08,408 --> 00:07:10,580
As it turns out,
those mushrooms in the forest

145
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:12,542
are in pretty high demand
around these parts

146
00:07:12,622 --> 00:07:13,873
because of the fragrance.

147
00:07:13,963 --> 00:07:15,755
So basically, you're loaded!

148
00:07:15,965 --> 00:07:17,627
-Treat us to dinner!
-[GODWIN] What?

149
00:07:18,007 --> 00:07:20,259
Why would I wanna
wine and dine you idiots?

150
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:21,921
Better yet,
why don't the two of you

151
00:07:22,011 --> 00:07:23,132
buy me something?

152
00:07:23,222 --> 00:07:24,674
No harm in helpin'
your friends,

153
00:07:24,764 --> 00:07:25,975
don't be stingy!

154
00:07:26,265 --> 00:07:27,847
-[laughing]
-Be a man, Godwin!

155
00:07:27,927 --> 00:07:29,889
-You guys are morons! Shut it!
-[all laughing]

156
00:07:29,979 --> 00:07:31,060
Takes one to know one, pal!

157
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:33,062
Would you boys
settle down and behave?

158
00:07:33,142 --> 00:07:35,564
The kids are showing you
all up, look at them work!

159
00:07:35,644 --> 00:07:36,645
-[ALL] Huh?
-[sighs]

160
00:07:36,735 --> 00:07:38,317
Looking good over here!

161
00:07:38,487 --> 00:07:39,608
-May I try?
-Huh.

162
00:07:40,569 --> 00:07:41,490
[chomps]

163
00:07:41,570 --> 00:07:44,112
Sir Hero's gonna love
all the nice stuff we have!

164
00:07:44,362 --> 00:07:45,944
Mm-hmm. I bet he will.

165
00:07:46,284 --> 00:07:47,575
No, they are not.

166
00:07:47,826 --> 00:07:50,578
[VAN] What you have described
to me is called decadence.

167
00:07:50,749 --> 00:07:52,200
It is not joy.

168
00:07:53,411 --> 00:07:54,622
-Hm.
-[indistinct chatter]

169
00:07:54,913 --> 00:07:56,334
[MALE VILLAGER 208A]
The Hero has returned!

170
00:07:56,414 --> 00:07:57,415
Huh.

171
00:07:58,005 --> 00:07:59,457
[indistinct chatter]

172
00:07:59,627 --> 00:08:00,668
Excellent.

173
00:08:00,838 --> 00:08:02,710
I hear you've
located the airship.

174
00:08:03,301 --> 00:08:04,261
Yes.

175
00:08:04,382 --> 00:08:06,764
Before that,
we would be most thrilled

176
00:08:06,844 --> 00:08:09,266
to have you all join us
in a celebratory toast.

177
00:08:09,556 --> 00:08:10,968
[FEMALE VILLAGER 208C]
Sir Hero!

178
00:08:11,058 --> 00:08:13,180
[MALE VILLAGER 208B]
Congratulations, Sir!

179
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:14,431
This again?

180
00:08:15,142 --> 00:08:16,643
What excessive revelry.

181
00:08:16,934 --> 00:08:17,934
-Hm?
-Huh?

182
00:08:18,935 --> 00:08:21,898
What he means is we
appreciate the thought, Mayor.

183
00:08:22,108 --> 00:08:24,531
But due to prior commitments,
we must refrain.

184
00:08:25,111 --> 00:08:26,112
[gasps]

185
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:27,944
I understand.

186
00:08:28,324 --> 00:08:30,537
Forgive our arrogance
and complete failure

187
00:08:30,617 --> 00:08:33,039
to take Sir Hero's obligations
into account.

188
00:08:33,329 --> 00:08:35,581
The citizens of Zoltan
pray to Lord Demis

189
00:08:35,661 --> 00:08:38,204
that Sir Hero finds
unwavering success.

190
00:08:38,794 --> 00:08:41,167
Prayers from heretics
won't reach the Almighty.

191
00:08:41,587 --> 00:08:42,708
-[MALE PRIEST 207A] Huh!
-[TORNED] Huh!

192
00:08:43,299 --> 00:08:50,305
♪

193
00:08:51,557 --> 00:08:52,558
Come now.

194
00:08:52,758 --> 00:08:54,469
That was highly offensive.

195
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:57,012
Take it back, Van.
And apologize.

196
00:08:57,682 --> 00:08:59,604
No. I will do neither.

197
00:09:00,565 --> 00:09:01,646
I am the Hero,

198
00:09:01,726 --> 00:09:03,688
who has undergone
training as a monk.

199
00:09:04,189 --> 00:09:06,321
One of my tasks
is to guide heretics

200
00:09:06,401 --> 00:09:07,572
onto the right path.

201
00:09:08,233 --> 00:09:09,654
[TISSE]
What is he talking about?

202
00:09:10,274 --> 00:09:11,906
The Divine Blessings
alone serve

203
00:09:11,986 --> 00:09:14,529
as obvious proof of devotion
to Lord Demis.

204
00:09:15,239 --> 00:09:16,911
Yet he calls us heretics?

205
00:09:17,491 --> 00:09:19,663
-[stomach growling]
-[groans]

206
00:09:20,454 --> 00:09:21,745
My stomach.

207
00:09:21,916 --> 00:09:24,288
♪

208
00:09:24,378 --> 00:09:27,921
Pardon me, but you do realize
you're being very insulting?

209
00:09:28,462 --> 00:09:31,505
You declare us to be heretics,
but for what reason?

210
00:09:31,885 --> 00:09:33,637
The fact that you live
such pointless,

211
00:09:33,717 --> 00:09:35,008
indolent lives here.

212
00:09:35,849 --> 00:09:38,972
According to scripture,
sloth is a mortal sin

213
00:09:39,052 --> 00:09:41,805
that conflicts with our roles
granted by the Almighty.

214
00:09:42,305 --> 00:09:44,858
You people must repent
and mend your ways.

215
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:48,191
The path before you is clear.

216
00:09:48,271 --> 00:09:51,444
♪

217
00:09:51,654 --> 00:09:54,026
[VAN] Take up arms against
the demonic troops!

218
00:09:54,737 --> 00:09:56,158
"Demonic troops?"

219
00:09:56,318 --> 00:09:57,490
"Take up arms?"

220
00:09:58,451 --> 00:10:00,372
You must fight
alongside the Hero.

221
00:10:00,703 --> 00:10:02,875
It is your sacred duty
to accept.

222
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:06,378
We have our land
and our livelihoods to protect!

223
00:10:06,498 --> 00:10:07,419
Be rational!

224
00:10:07,499 --> 00:10:08,500
Cast it aside.

225
00:10:09,881 --> 00:10:12,674
This pedestrian backwater
is utterly worthless.

226
00:10:12,964 --> 00:10:15,176
[indistinct chatter]

227
00:10:15,257 --> 00:10:16,258
[TISSE]
Uh-oh.

228
00:10:18,139 --> 00:10:20,141
Our grandparents
endured hardship

229
00:10:20,221 --> 00:10:22,594
and put their lives on the line
to develop our home!

230
00:10:23,014 --> 00:10:24,806
And yet you call it worthless?

231
00:10:25,056 --> 00:10:26,397
Even as the Hero,

232
00:10:26,557 --> 00:10:28,850
to say such a thing
is beyond rude!

233
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:30,101
Rude?

234
00:10:30,351 --> 00:10:32,523
Etiquette describes
mortal norms.

235
00:10:33,024 --> 00:10:34,945
I am speaking of the divine.

236
00:10:35,065 --> 00:10:40,611
♪

237
00:10:44,034 --> 00:10:45,495
Why do they deny me?

238
00:10:45,866 --> 00:10:46,957
It's simple.

239
00:10:47,077 --> 00:10:49,579
You just insulted their home
right in front of them.

240
00:10:50,170 --> 00:10:52,122
Their Zoltan is dearly beloved.

241
00:10:52,372 --> 00:10:54,374
They cherish
their peaceful lives here.

242
00:10:55,335 --> 00:10:56,336
[sighs]

243
00:10:57,927 --> 00:10:59,259
This is a nuisance.

244
00:10:59,719 --> 00:11:00,680
[clangs]

245
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,512
Huh? What are you up to?

246
00:11:02,682 --> 00:11:03,723
[ESTA]
Stop, Van!

247
00:11:04,514 --> 00:11:06,305
[LAVENDER]
Do not get in Van's way.

248
00:11:06,686 --> 00:11:07,597
Move aside!

249
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:10,059
Van's intentions are not
borne out of heroism,

250
00:11:10,139 --> 00:11:11,230
but desperation!

251
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,062
Oh, I know what he's doing.

252
00:11:13,272 --> 00:11:14,854
And I really don't care.

253
00:11:15,024 --> 00:11:17,066
The way I see it,
anything Van does

254
00:11:17,146 --> 00:11:18,947
is completely
within his rights.

255
00:11:20,699 --> 00:11:21,700
Hm.

256
00:11:22,030 --> 00:11:23,071
♪

257
00:11:23,201 --> 00:11:24,363
[Esta and Mistorm grunting]

258
00:11:25,784 --> 00:11:26,905
[MISTORM ]
Could it be?

259
00:11:27,456 --> 00:11:28,957
This is sorcery!

260
00:11:29,207 --> 00:11:30,208
[grunts]

261
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:32,831
Cardinal!

262
00:11:33,411 --> 00:11:34,622
[cigar crackling]

263
00:11:34,712 --> 00:11:35,964
-[exhales]
-[wind whooshing]

264
00:11:36,124 --> 00:11:39,087
Failure can be a harsh teacher
in Van's education.

265
00:11:39,217 --> 00:11:41,589
Anyway, the bodies
of a few small-town peasants

266
00:11:41,669 --> 00:11:43,551
will not stain
the Hero's reputation,

267
00:11:43,631 --> 00:11:45,132
if we're being
perfectly honest.

268
00:11:45,263 --> 00:11:46,223
What?

269
00:11:46,424 --> 00:11:48,636
[LAVENDER] No funny tricks
from you either, Tisse.

270
00:11:49,517 --> 00:11:51,519
Any sudden moves,
and I'll kill you.

271
00:11:52,389 --> 00:11:53,681
[groaning]

272
00:11:54,812 --> 00:11:57,604
Behold.
The shield of the Fairy King.

273
00:11:58,275 --> 00:11:59,686
It has the power to guide you

274
00:11:59,776 --> 00:12:01,488
to the correct path
and save you.

275
00:12:03,740 --> 00:12:06,653
Your denial of the Hero
for a life of idleness

276
00:12:06,743 --> 00:12:08,575
has been judged by Lord Demis.

277
00:12:09,786 --> 00:12:13,159
Now, let us fight
the demon lord's army together!

278
00:12:16,202 --> 00:12:19,005
-[YARANDRALA] Thorn Bind!
-[rumbling]

279
00:12:19,085 --> 00:12:20,206
What is this?

280
00:12:21,417 --> 00:12:22,548
[YARANDRALA]
Van the Hero.

281
00:12:22,668 --> 00:12:24,380
Is this truly necessary?

282
00:12:24,630 --> 00:12:25,671
Who are you?

283
00:12:26,552 --> 00:12:29,385
Your neighborhood
high elf residing in Zoltan.

284
00:12:29,675 --> 00:12:30,676
[sighs]

285
00:12:31,807 --> 00:12:34,269
What hero resorts
to mind control magic?

286
00:12:34,389 --> 00:12:36,351
That is the work of a villain.

287
00:12:36,602 --> 00:12:38,433
You dare liken me to a villain?

288
00:12:39,024 --> 00:12:41,226
Who are you to speak
on right and wrong?

289
00:12:42,898 --> 00:12:43,899
[thuds]

290
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:47,982
I the Hero, Van,
slayer of evil!

291
00:12:49,074 --> 00:12:50,535
Stinger Weeds, unleash!

292
00:12:50,615 --> 00:12:51,986
[rumbling]

293
00:12:52,116 --> 00:12:54,038
[clanging]

294
00:12:54,789 --> 00:12:56,160
-[thuds]
-[grunts]

295
00:12:56,911 --> 00:12:57,912
[grunts]

296
00:12:58,122 --> 00:13:00,875
♪

297
00:13:00,955 --> 00:13:01,956
Hm.

298
00:13:02,586 --> 00:13:04,498
[indistinct chatter]

299
00:13:04,628 --> 00:13:06,710
-Party's over, we gotta run!
-Hurry, get to safety!

300
00:13:08,592 --> 00:13:09,593
[grunts]

301
00:13:11,595 --> 00:13:12,596
[grunts]

302
00:13:12,756 --> 00:13:15,509
♪

303
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:17,851
Martial Art.

304
00:13:18,351 --> 00:13:20,894
Destructive Comet Kick!

305
00:13:22,065 --> 00:13:23,066
[thumps]

306
00:13:25,358 --> 00:13:27,650
[screaming]

307
00:13:28,271 --> 00:13:29,272
Close one.

308
00:13:29,732 --> 00:13:30,573
Danan.

309
00:13:30,653 --> 00:13:32,775
Gutsy of you
to take on a Hero alone.

310
00:13:33,156 --> 00:13:34,277
I've got your back.

311
00:13:34,737 --> 00:13:36,409
Do you know
what you're getting into?

312
00:13:36,619 --> 00:13:37,660
Pretty obvious.

313
00:13:38,581 --> 00:13:40,533
He can mend himself
as the Hero.

314
00:13:40,783 --> 00:13:42,875
Why refuse to apply
Healing Hands?

315
00:13:43,085 --> 00:13:44,126
Who's to say?

316
00:13:44,877 --> 00:13:46,208
[YARANDRALA]
His body may be durable,

317
00:13:46,288 --> 00:13:47,669
but not indestructible.

318
00:13:48,841 --> 00:13:50,042
Two great evils!

319
00:13:50,462 --> 00:13:51,843
But I am the Hero.

320
00:13:52,754 --> 00:13:54,046
I will not succumb!

321
00:13:54,506 --> 00:13:55,507
There's your answer.

322
00:13:55,927 --> 00:13:57,639
This kid won't
stay down for good

323
00:13:57,719 --> 00:13:59,721
because of the faith
he has in his Blessing.

324
00:14:00,552 --> 00:14:03,354
Time to kick his butt
and take him down a peg.

325
00:14:04,646 --> 00:14:05,687
Lord Demis,

326
00:14:05,897 --> 00:14:07,899
I present to you
a Hero's fight.

327
00:14:11,192 --> 00:14:14,235
Martial Art,
Fierce Tiger Claws! [echo]

328
00:14:14,615 --> 00:14:16,737
Martial Art, Holy Blade!
[echo]

329
00:14:17,368 --> 00:14:18,369
[grunts]

330
00:14:19,950 --> 00:14:23,374
♪

331
00:14:23,624 --> 00:14:24,875
[groans]

332
00:14:24,955 --> 00:14:26,126
Just one hit.

333
00:14:26,376 --> 00:14:28,669
[rumbling]

334
00:14:29,329 --> 00:14:30,500
[thumps]

335
00:14:31,001 --> 00:14:32,082
[groans]

336
00:14:32,753 --> 00:14:34,214
[grunts]

337
00:14:34,925 --> 00:14:35,926
[grunts]

338
00:14:36,716 --> 00:14:38,638
[grunts]
It hurts.

339
00:14:39,259 --> 00:14:42,182
But...a Hero must not yield.

340
00:14:42,392 --> 00:14:44,594
[grunts]
Healing Hands Mastery. [echo]

341
00:14:45,184 --> 00:14:46,185
Reflect.
[echo]

342
00:14:47,727 --> 00:14:49,348
[grunting]

343
00:14:50,349 --> 00:14:52,271
[groans]

344
00:14:52,521 --> 00:14:53,522
[VAN]
Amazing.

345
00:14:53,693 --> 00:14:55,444
I suffered immense pain
from that,

346
00:14:55,604 --> 00:14:56,906
yet you still stand.

347
00:14:57,526 --> 00:14:59,858
You are a worthy opponent
for the Hero.

348
00:15:00,319 --> 00:15:01,320
Danan!

349
00:15:03,072 --> 00:15:05,244
So you reflected
the injury right back?

350
00:15:05,784 --> 00:15:07,866
Pretty low stunt if you ask me.

351
00:15:08,367 --> 00:15:10,288
[VAN] That stunt
that allows me to heal

352
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:12,080
using my opponent's vitality,

353
00:15:12,581 --> 00:15:15,924
with it, I can thwart
any dire situation at will.

354
00:15:16,424 --> 00:15:18,216
No matter how great the evil,

355
00:15:18,296 --> 00:15:19,928
the Hero will not give in.

356
00:15:20,468 --> 00:15:23,091
What kind of Hero
passes his pain off to others?

357
00:15:23,471 --> 00:15:25,263
Ain't nothin' heroic about it!

358
00:15:25,383 --> 00:15:26,384
[spits]

359
00:15:26,764 --> 00:15:28,186
The Almighty Lord Demis

360
00:15:28,266 --> 00:15:30,097
designed me
with my role in mind.

361
00:15:31,228 --> 00:15:33,561
Condemnation is
a rejection of His will.

362
00:15:34,271 --> 00:15:35,943
There is no greater heresy.

363
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:37,895
Hm.

364
00:15:38,025 --> 00:15:40,487
♪

365
00:15:41,488 --> 00:15:43,360
[roaring]

366
00:15:43,490 --> 00:15:44,491
Huh?!

367
00:15:45,952 --> 00:15:48,075
[SALT DRAGON 208A] Murderer
of our fallen brethren.

368
00:15:48,615 --> 00:15:50,537
Thief of our stolen treasure.

369
00:15:50,747 --> 00:15:53,330
The time has come for you
to taste our wrath

370
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:54,791
and vengeance!

371
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:56,292
Those wicked dragons.

372
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:59,085
Have they come to rob me
of my shield?

373
00:15:59,415 --> 00:16:02,418
[growling]

374
00:16:03,299 --> 00:16:05,341
[YARANDRALA]
O, spirit of the mighty tree!

375
00:16:05,551 --> 00:16:09,175
♪

376
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,387
[explosion]

377
00:16:11,557 --> 00:16:14,139
♪

378
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:15,981
My powers
are not a favorable match

379
00:16:16,061 --> 00:16:17,603
against the salt dragons,
but...

380
00:16:18,183 --> 00:16:20,145
Zoltan will be charred
at this rate!

381
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:22,818
-Yes! That is just what I fear!
-Now, fall!

382
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:24,609
Huh. Get lost!

383
00:16:24,940 --> 00:16:26,741
O, spirit of the mighty tree!

384
00:16:26,822 --> 00:16:29,824
[explosion]

385
00:16:30,325 --> 00:16:31,656
This is such a shame.

386
00:16:31,906 --> 00:16:33,658
The only shame
I see is standing

387
00:16:33,748 --> 00:16:35,790
right in front of me,
not helping anyone!

388
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:38,252
I will not counter
the Lord's will.

389
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:42,006
If the salt dragons
do destroy this sinful land,

390
00:16:42,757 --> 00:16:44,258
then no choice will remain.

391
00:16:44,338 --> 00:16:45,760
Even the sloths of Zoltan

392
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:47,631
will join the war
in retaliation.

393
00:16:48,052 --> 00:16:49,263
Okay, I've heard enough

394
00:16:49,343 --> 00:16:51,175
of your crappy
sermons, little man.

395
00:16:51,345 --> 00:16:53,097
I'm taking you down first!

396
00:16:53,177 --> 00:16:54,178
[thumps]

397
00:16:55,179 --> 00:16:57,561
[grunts]
Healing Hands Mastery.

398
00:16:57,851 --> 00:16:58,892
Reflect.

399
00:17:00,354 --> 00:17:01,685
[groans]

400
00:17:02,145 --> 00:17:03,727
[explosion]

401
00:17:05,028 --> 00:17:06,940
-[screams]
-[sword clangs]

402
00:17:07,691 --> 00:17:08,692
[grunts]

403
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:10,864
Sorry we're late.

404
00:17:11,194 --> 00:17:12,115
You're back!

405
00:17:12,195 --> 00:17:13,656
Thought you were still gone.

406
00:17:15,038 --> 00:17:16,239
-[grunts]
-[sword clanging]

407
00:17:17,450 --> 00:17:18,451
[grunts]

408
00:17:20,042 --> 00:17:22,295
-What was that?
-[shield whirring]

409
00:17:24,497 --> 00:17:25,498
[chuckles]

410
00:17:25,918 --> 00:17:26,959
[VAN]
Why, you...

411
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:29,551
[swords clanging]

412
00:17:29,712 --> 00:17:31,053
[grunts]

413
00:17:31,804 --> 00:17:32,805
[grunts]

414
00:17:32,965 --> 00:17:39,971
♪

415
00:17:41,012 --> 00:17:42,013
Huh.

416
00:17:43,565 --> 00:17:44,566
Hm.

417
00:17:44,726 --> 00:17:48,359
♪

418
00:17:48,690 --> 00:17:49,901
[RED]
Here come the dragons.

419
00:17:50,271 --> 00:17:52,073
Van's on my tail too, no doubt.

420
00:17:53,444 --> 00:17:55,026
Hey, you. Nice work.

421
00:17:56,197 --> 00:17:58,279
Without your threads,
Mr. Crawly Wally,

422
00:17:58,659 --> 00:18:00,281
I never would've
made it in time.

423
00:18:00,491 --> 00:18:01,872
[squealing]

424
00:18:02,493 --> 00:18:03,994
Now, for the fun part.

425
00:18:04,495 --> 00:18:06,917
Making sure his heroic efforts
aren't all for nothing.

426
00:18:07,087 --> 00:18:09,379
-[growling]
-[grunts]

427
00:18:10,791 --> 00:18:11,882
Just hear me out!

428
00:18:12,042 --> 00:18:14,965
[growling]

429
00:18:15,635 --> 00:18:18,889
♪

430
00:18:19,219 --> 00:18:21,301
[SALT DRAGON 208A]
Immense bloodlust.

431
00:18:21,511 --> 00:18:23,223
-The Hero.
-Huh.

432
00:18:23,683 --> 00:18:25,105
[RED]
Listen carefully, okay?

433
00:18:25,725 --> 00:18:26,686
Relax.

434
00:18:26,806 --> 00:18:28,938
I ran here
so I could return this.

435
00:18:29,769 --> 00:18:31,230
Yours to begin with, right?

436
00:18:31,941 --> 00:18:33,863
-[thuds]
-Indeed.

437
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:37,697
The former demon lord entrusted
us with that treasure.

438
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:38,868
I knew it.

439
00:18:39,698 --> 00:18:40,699
Then take it back.

440
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:47,576
♪

441
00:18:50,249 --> 00:18:52,461
[SALT DRAGON 208A]
Beware of that Hero.

442
00:18:52,631 --> 00:18:54,543
♪

443
00:18:54,713 --> 00:18:56,505
It's kind of you
to offer a waring.

444
00:18:57,045 --> 00:18:58,637
-But it's too late.
-Martial Art.

445
00:18:58,967 --> 00:19:00,719
Holy Blade!

446
00:19:00,969 --> 00:19:02,550
[rumbling]

447
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:03,681
[thudding]

448
00:19:06,804 --> 00:19:07,845
[RED]
Oh, boy.

449
00:19:08,346 --> 00:19:10,188
That's gonna give
travelers a headache.

450
00:19:11,309 --> 00:19:13,441
Sorry, but you fail as a Hero.

451
00:19:13,981 --> 00:19:15,192
Another heretic.

452
00:19:15,653 --> 00:19:18,485
There!
[groaning]

453
00:19:18,696 --> 00:19:20,658
[RED]
If you can't swing your blade,

454
00:19:20,988 --> 00:19:22,990
you won't be
cutting anyone down.

455
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:25,322
[VAN]
How dare you? Release me!

456
00:19:26,323 --> 00:19:28,205
All that work
to level your Blessing,

457
00:19:28,825 --> 00:19:30,707
when you should've focused
on your sword.

458
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:32,829
The methods of men
have no merit.

459
00:19:33,079 --> 00:19:35,422
It is nothing in the face
of my Divine Blessing!

460
00:19:35,962 --> 00:19:36,923
[RED]
Got it.

461
00:19:37,043 --> 00:19:38,755
So that's what makes you tick.

462
00:19:39,175 --> 00:19:41,337
Explains why I could
lure you out of town

463
00:19:41,427 --> 00:19:42,679
just like that,

464
00:19:42,929 --> 00:19:44,881
away from the safety
of your party.

465
00:19:46,052 --> 00:19:48,014
If my sword fails,
I have magic!

466
00:19:48,804 --> 00:19:50,726
[grunts]

467
00:19:51,437 --> 00:19:53,849
Good luck using
any magic at this range.

468
00:19:54,270 --> 00:19:56,352
Is this some plot
to stall for time?

469
00:19:56,892 --> 00:19:58,444
The Hero can fight
through nightfall

470
00:19:58,524 --> 00:19:59,815
and not be out of breath!

471
00:20:00,105 --> 00:20:02,648
Oh, we'll have this wrapped up
way before nightfall.

472
00:20:03,108 --> 00:20:04,570
-Won't we?
-[gasps]

473
00:20:07,282 --> 00:20:08,453
Oh!

474
00:20:08,653 --> 00:20:09,865
[thumps]

475
00:20:12,827 --> 00:20:14,039
[thudding]

476
00:20:15,580 --> 00:20:18,583
[thudding]

477
00:20:20,625 --> 00:20:21,666
[grunts]
Ow!

478
00:20:21,756 --> 00:20:22,797
[groans]

479
00:20:23,548 --> 00:20:24,549
[thuds]

480
00:20:24,629 --> 00:20:26,510
Don't bother trying
to figure it out.

481
00:20:26,921 --> 00:20:29,343
You'll forget me by tomorrow.
[blows]

482
00:20:29,764 --> 00:20:31,305
His party will be here soon.

483
00:20:31,725 --> 00:20:33,677
Let's get going
before they see us.

484
00:20:33,978 --> 00:20:34,979
Hm.

485
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:40,564
[VAN]
So cold.

486
00:20:41,895 --> 00:20:45,188
Ah. My death is imminent.

487
00:20:46,029 --> 00:20:47,741
The Hero was defeated.

488
00:20:51,114 --> 00:20:52,445
Then let it be so.

489
00:20:53,496 --> 00:20:56,329
The only duty of the Hero
is to fight evil.

490
00:20:57,580 --> 00:20:58,661
Not to win.

491
00:20:59,792 --> 00:21:02,205
In the end, I did
what was asked of me.

492
00:21:03,706 --> 00:21:06,799
But. Why must it be that girl?

493
00:21:08,631 --> 00:21:11,844
If everything proceeds
according to Lord Demis' will,

494
00:21:13,095 --> 00:21:17,349
then surely I met that
girl for a reason.

495
00:21:20,222 --> 00:21:21,473
[ESTA]
He's losing consciousness!

496
00:21:22,934 --> 00:21:24,105
[VAN]
I see.

497
00:21:24,276 --> 00:21:31,232
♪

498
00:21:31,733 --> 00:21:32,904
Healing Hands.

499
00:21:33,114 --> 00:21:38,239
♪

500
00:21:38,539 --> 00:21:40,331
[gasps]
Look! He's alive!

501
00:21:40,581 --> 00:21:42,663
Are you okay? I'm here!

502
00:21:43,044 --> 00:21:45,046
I won't leave you alone
ever again!

503
00:21:45,336 --> 00:21:46,337
[VAN]
Hm.

504
00:21:47,548 --> 00:21:49,420
So this is part of my role.

505
00:21:51,091 --> 00:21:52,092
Van?

506
00:21:53,093 --> 00:21:54,805
I will kill that girl.

507
00:21:56,056 --> 00:21:59,009
And at last I will be
the true Hero.

508
00:21:59,309 --> 00:22:02,812
♪

509
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:04,184
[VAN]
The Lord is come!

510
00:22:04,644 --> 00:22:07,647
[laughing]

